algorithm: New algorithm: The new algorithm calculates the scores for the bins by taking the exponentiated product of the item size and the maximum capacity, then dividing it by the sum of the logarithms of the rest capacities of the bins divided by the logarithm of the sum of the rest capacities.
code:
import numpy as np
import math

def score(item: int, bins: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:
    max_capacity = np.max(bins)
    rest_capacity = max_capacity - bins
    rest_capacity_sum = np.sum(rest_capacity)
    scores = np.exp(item * max_capacity) / (np.sum(np.log(rest_capacity)) / np.log(rest_capacity_sum))
    return scores
